@Starsplash_85: Have you tried 2007's language packs? I did some searching, and it seems that 2007's language packs work with Office 2010. Try it out.

@ryoslayer: After the install, you can do whatever you want with the install files. If you are a true pirate, burn the files to a disk and pass it on to someone who needs it. Keep the files circulating.

@raindeuxx: When you receive the error "Could not download because an important file is either missing or corrupted", redownload. It means that either the download didn't finish completely, or someone seeding has messed with a file and you got a messed file.

@demonster: For people who have been instructed to download msxml 6.10.1129, make sure you do all system updates before trying to install.

@UnderworldDemon666  thanks for this upload. Finally it works.
On first install it failed, but after set its compatibility with my OS, installation work. 
Then i run activator to remove pop up for activation. Really work great now.
